<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-080-788  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 080 788.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Design  Feb 9 1989 v37 n3 p25(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fuzzy logic microprocessor tackles real-time tasks. (TechnologyAdvances)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Waller, Larry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Togai InfraLogic Inc FC110 is a microprocessor for fuzzy-logicprogramming aimed at real-time commercial applications.andP;  Fuzzylogic is being used in artificial intelligence work that it donein real time.andP;  It is a framework designed for quantifyingnonprecise values in programmed algorithms.andP;  Togai claims theFC110 operates about 20 times faster than an 80386-based system inrunning key inferencing statements in optimized instruction rules.andO;Rule-execution-rate performance shows similar gains.andP;  The FC110requires 35 micro-seconds per evaluation, as compared with 440micro-seconds.andP;  The product's architecture is similar to an 8-bitRISC processor, with specially tailored instruction set andaddressing modes.andP;  Prototypes of the FC110 are expected by Jun1989.andP;  Samples will be available for $90 shortly after.andP;  Togaiintroduced earlier in 1989 a fuzzy-C compiler that runs onhigh-performance desktop processors.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Togai InfraLogic Inc. (product development).andO;Product:   Togai InfraLogic FC110 (Microprocessor) (product development).andO;Topic:     Microprocessors8-BitArtificial intelligenceProduct DevelopmentFuzzy sets.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Data flow among elements in fuzzy logic microprocessor. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>